An definition file is either a Interface Definition file (*.idl) or a type library file (*.tlb). A type library can be linked into a component (*.ocx, *.dll, *.exe, ...)
A marshaller DLL can be generated from an IDL file. If generated, the marshaller DLL will automatically be registered by the Wizard.

The EiffelCOM Wizard can backup files it overwrites by adding the extension '.bac'.
